member.summary:
            Gets or sets measurement noise covariance matrix (R). [p x p] matrix.

Variance inaccuracy of detected location. 
            It is usually defined as scalar, therefore it can be set as: Matrix.Diagonal(MeasurementVectorDimension, [value]);

            Linear acceleration model for 2D case.

Vector is composed as: [X, vX, aX, Y, vY, aY]
            Model is constructed as following:
            p(i) = p(i-1) + (Δt) * v(i-1) + ((Δt)^2 / 2) * a(t-1);
            v(i) = v(i-1) + (Δt) * a(t-1);
            a(t) = a(t-1);


Look at: http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/acons.html

            Linear acceleration model for 2D case.

Vector is composed as: [X, vX, Y, vY]
            Model is constructed as following:
            p(i) = p(i-1) + (Δt) * v(i-1);
            v(i) = v(i-1);
